%% Data Flow Diagram - llama-stack-k8s-operator
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / kubectl
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Operator as LlamaStackDistribution<br/>Reconciler
    participant Kustomize as Kustomize Renderer
    participant LlamaServer as Llama Stack Server<br/>8321/TCP HTTP

    Note over User,LlamaServer: Flow 1: LlamaStackDistribution Reconciliation

    User->>K8sAPI: Create/Update LlamaStackDistribution CR
    K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch event (HTTPS/443, SA Token)
    Operator->>Kustomize: Render embedded manifests<br/>(name-prefix, namespace, field mutations)
    Kustomize-->>Operator: Rendered YAML resources

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create/Update Deployment<br/>(HTTPS/443, SA Token)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create/Update Service<br/>(HTTPS/443, SA Token)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create PVC (if storage configured)<br/>(HTTPS/443, SA Token)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create/Update ServiceAccount<br/>(HTTPS/443, SA Token)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create/Update ClusterRoleBinding<br/>(HTTPS/443, SA Token)

    Note over Operator,LlamaServer: Health Check Phase

    Operator->>LlamaServer: GET /v1/health (HTTP/8321)
    LlamaServer-->>Operator: Health status
    Operator->>LlamaServer: GET /v1/providers (HTTP/8321)
    LlamaServer-->>Operator: Provider info
    Operator->>LlamaServer: GET /v1/version (HTTP/8321)
    LlamaServer-->>Operator: Version info

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Update LlamaStackDistribution/status<br/>(HTTPS/443, SA Token)

    Note over User,LlamaServer: Flow 2: ConfigMap Change Detection

    User->>K8sAPI: Update ConfigMap (user config or CA bundle)
    K8sAPI->>Operator: ConfigMap watch event (HTTPS/443, SA Token)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: List LlamaStackDistributions<br/>matching ConfigMap (HTTPS/443, SA Token)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Update Deployment annotations<br/>to trigger pod restart (HTTPS/443, SA Token)
